result.execSummary:
The defendant Cody A. Anderson was found guilty of the following charge(s) in this case.

  • Burglary-Building or Dwelling [Modifiers: PTAC, as a Party to a Crime], a class F felony, Wisconsin Statutes 943.10(1m)(a).

Charge(s) in this case were read in to this or other case(s). A "read in" charge is a charge that is dismissed as part of a plea agreement, however:

  • The defendant agrees to have the court consider the charge(s) when sentencing for another crime, under Wis. Stats. 973.20(1g)(b); and
  • The defendant cannot be prosecuted for these charge(s) in the future.

Notice to employers: It may be a violation of state law to discriminate against a job applicant because of an arrest or conviction record. Generally speaking, an employer may refuse to hire an applicant on the basis of a conviction only if the circumstances of the conviction substantially relate to the particular job. For more information, see Wisconsin Statute 111.335 and the Department of Workforce Development's publication, Arrest and Conviction Records under the Law.

miscConds.notes: Defendant to pay costs and DNA surcharge within 60 days (6/10/16) through the Dodge County Clerk of Courts office or set up a payment plan within said time.

Defendant shall not have any direct or indirect contact or communication with co-defendants.

Defendant shall not go near or on the premises of victim, G.P. at any time.

Defendant shall not consume alcohol or other intoxicants. Defendant must maintain absolute sobriety and shall not go upon the premises of any establishment whose primary business activity involves the sale or distribution of alcoholic beverages, including bars, taverns, liquor stores and beer tents.

Defendant shall not use/purchase/possess/control any controlled substances (without a valid prescription therefore) or drug paraphernalia, nor be in the presence of anyone who does.

Must obtain/maintain full-time employment or schooling or a combination of both.

Must submit to random urinalysis.

Defendant shall write a letter of apology to victims, G.P. and D.W. within the first 60 days. Letter to be reviewed by Agent.

Defendant shall undergo and successfully complete AODA Assessment and follow through with any recommendations resulting therefrom.

Defendant shall participate in and complete all treatment directed by Agent, including Thinking for a Change.
